<%# /cfo -- role-specific sales page for CFOs / finance leaders (esp. PE-backed &
    multi-entity). Sells OTP on its own. Sibling of /cio, reframed for the P&L
    owner: AI is a growing line item with no proven return; cost-to-contribution
    per seat (human or agent); runaway agent spend; bring-your-own-rates;
    portfolio consolidation. v7 layout, v7.css PREBUILT -> scoped .cfo-* CSS +
    inline styles only (no new Tailwind utils). %>
<% var _v = (typeof assetVersion !== 'undefined' ? assetVersion : 'dev'); %>
<style>
  .cfo-sec   { padding-top: 84px; padding-bottom: 84px; }
  .cfo-wrap  { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; padding-left: 24px; padding-right: 24px; }
  .cfo-center{ text-align: center; }
  .cfo-paper { background: var(--white, #fcfcfd); }
  .cfo-grey  { background: var(--grey, #f0f1f3); }
  @media (max-width: 640px){ .cfo-sec { padding-top: 54px; padding-bottom: 54px; } }

  .cfo-eyebrow { font-family:'Schibsted Grotesk','Inter',sans-serif; font-weight:800; font-size:12px; letter-spacing:.14em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--ink-mute,#888c96); display:flex; align-items:center; gap:10px; }
  .cfo-tick { width:8px; height:8px; border-radius:50%; background:var(--orgy,#a8e63a); display:inline-block; }
  .cfo-h1 { font-family:'Schibsted Grotesk','Inter',sans-serif; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:-0.025em; line-height:1.05; font-size:clamp(2.2rem,4.6vw,3.5rem); color:var(--ink,#14161c); margin:0; max-width:18ch; }
  .cfo-h2 { font-family:'Schibsted Grotesk','Inter',sans-serif; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:-0.02em; line-height:1.12; font-size:clamp(1.7rem,3.2vw,2.5rem); color:var(--ink,#14161c); }
  .cfo-lead { font-size:18px; line-height:1.62; color:var(--ink-soft,#494d57); }
  .cfo-body { font-size:16px; line-height:1.65; color:var(--ink-soft,#494d57); }
  .cfo-max720 { max-width:720px; }
  .accent { color:var(--blue,#0d7df2); } .accent-g { color:var(--green-deep,#06724a); }

  .cfo-btn  { display:inline-flex; align-items:center; gap:8px; padding:14px 28px; font-size:16px; font-weight:700; border-radius:12px; text-decoration:none; white-space:nowrap; }
  .cfo-btn.primary { background:var(--blue,#0d7df2); color:#fff; box-shadow:0 10px 26px -10px rgba(13,125,242,.6); transition:transform .15s ease, box-shadow .15s ease; }
  .cfo-btn.primary:hover { transform:translateY(-1px); box-shadow:0 14px 30px -10px rgba(13,125,242,.7); }
  .cfo-btn.ghost { background:transparent; color:var(--ink,#14161c); border:1px solid var(--line,#e6e8ec); }
  .cfo-btn.ghost:hover { border-color:#c8ccd4; }
  .cfo-cta-row { display:flex; gap:12px; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-top:30px; }

  .cfo-grid3 { display:grid; gap:18px; grid-template-columns:1fr; margin-top:36px; }
  @media (min-width:780px){ .cfo-grid3 { grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr); } }
  .cfo-grid2 { display:grid; gap:18px; grid-template-columns:1fr; margin-top:36px; }
  @media (min-width:780px){ .cfo-grid2 { grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr); } }
  .cfo-card { background:var(--white,#fcfcfd); border:1px solid var(--line,#e6e8ec); border-radius:16px; padding:24px 22px; box-shadow:0 10px 28px rgba(20,22,28,.05); }
  .cfo-card h3 { font-family:'Schibsted Grotesk',sans-serif; font-weight:700; font-size:18px; color:var(--ink,#14161c); margin:0 0 8px; }
  .cfo-card p { font-size:14.5px; line-height:1.6; color:var(--ink-soft,#494d57); margin:0; }
  .cfo-chip { display:inline-flex; width:38px; height:38px; border-radius:11px; align-items:center; justify-content:center; margin-bottom:14px; }

  .cfo-feat { display:grid; gap:2px 28px; grid-template-columns:1fr; margin-top:34px; }
  @media (min-width:720px){ .cfo-feat { grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; } }
  .cfo-feat-row { display:flex; gap:13px; align-items:flex-start; padding:15px 0; border-bottom:1px solid var(--line,#e6e8ec); }
  .cfo-feat-row svg { flex:none; margin-top:2px; }
  .cfo-feat-row b { font-family:'Schibsted Grotesk',sans-serif; font-weight:700; font-size:15px; color:var(--ink,#14161c); display:block; }
  .cfo-feat-row span { font-size:13.5px; line-height:1.55; color:var(--ink-soft,#494d57); }

  .cfo-quoteband { background:linear-gradient(180deg,#f2f7ff 0%, #eef3fb 100%); border-top:1px solid var(--line,#e6e8ec); border-bottom:1px solid var(--line,#e6e8ec); }
  .cfo-qmark { display:block; font-family:'Schibsted Grotesk',serif; font-weight:900; font-size:64px; line-height:.3; color:var(--orgy-deep,#8BC42A); }
  .cfo-quote { font-family:'Schibsted Grotesk',sans-serif; font-weight:600; font-size:clamp(1.35rem,2.6vw,1.9rem); line-height:1.4; letter-spacing:-0.01em; color:var(--ink,#14161c); }
  .cfo-quote .accent { color:var(--blue,#0d7df2); }
  .cfo-cite { font-size:13px; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:.04em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--ink-mute,#888c96); margin-top:18px; }

  .cfo-trust-strip { display:flex; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:8px 14px; margin-top:30px; font-size:12px; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:.06em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--ink-mute,#888c96); }
  .cfo-trust-strip b { color:var(--ink-soft,#494d57); }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference){
    body.cfo-anim .reveal { opacity:0; transform:translateY(18px); transition:opacity .7s cubic-bezier(.16,1,.3,1), transform .7s cubic-bezier(.16,1,.3,1); }
    body.cfo-anim .reveal.in { opacity:1; transform:none; }
  }

  /* ===== animated hero scene: seats roll up into the operating plan ===== */
  .cfo-hero { background:var(--white,#fcfcfd); overflow:hidden; }
  .cfo-hero-wrap { max-width:1240px; margin:0 auto; padding:120px 24px 60px; }
  .cfo-hero-grid { display:flex; gap:40px; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap; }
  .cfo-hero-copy { flex:1 1 430px; min-width:330px; padding-top:8px; }
  .cfo-stage { flex:0 0 560px; position:relative; width:560px; height:500px; }
  .rise { opacity:0; animation:f-rise .7s cubic-bezier(.16,1,.3,1) forwards; }
  @keyframes f-rise { from{opacity:0; transform:translateY(16px);} to{opacity:1; transform:translateY(0);} }
  .pop { opacity:0; animation:f-pop .55s cubic-bezier(.34,1.4,.5,1) forwards; }
  @keyframes f-pop { from{opacity:0; transform:scale(.9);} to{opacity:1; transform:scale(1);} }

  .f-conn { position:absolute; inset:0; z-index:1; pointer-events:none; overflow:visible; }
  .f-conn path { fill:none; stroke-width:2; stroke-linecap:round; stroke-dasharray:1; stroke-dashoffset:1; animation:f-draw 1.1s ease forwards; }
  @keyframes f-draw { to{stroke-dashoffset:0;} }

  .f-board { position:absolute; left:120px; top:6px; width:320px; z-index:4; background:var(--card,#fff); border:1px solid var(--line,#e6e8ec); border-radius:16px; box-shadow:0 18px 44px -16px rgba(20,22,28,.28); padding:14px 16px; }
  .f-board-h { display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:space-between; margin-bottom:10px; }
  .f-board-t { font-family:'Schibsted Grotesk',sans-serif; font-weight:800; font-size:12.5px; letter-spacing:.04em; color:var(--ink,#14161c); }
  .f-live { display:inline-flex; align-items:center; gap:5px; font-size:10px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:.04em; color:var(--green-deep,#06724a); }
  .f-live i { width:6px; height:6px; border-radius:50%; background:var(--green,#0a9d63); animation:f-dot 1.8s ease-in-out infinite; }
  @keyframes f-dot { 0%,100%{box-shadow:0 0 0 0 rgba(10,157,99,.5);} 50%{box-shadow:0 0 0 5px rgba(10,157,99,0);} }
  .f-kpi { display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:space-between; gap:10px; padding:7px 0; border-top:1px solid var(--line,#eef0f3); }
  .f-kpi:first-of-type { border-top:0; }
  .f-kpi-name { font-size:12.5px; color:var(--ink-soft,#494d57); display:flex; align-items:center; gap:7px; }
  .f-owner { width:17px; height:17px; border-radius:5px; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; font-size:9px; font-weight:800; color:#fff; font-family:'Schibsted Grotesk',sans-serif; }
  .f-kpi-val { font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace; font-size:12.5px; font-weight:600; color:var(--ink,#14161c); }
  .f-pill { font-size:10px; font-weight:800; padding:2px 8px; border-radius:999px; }
  .f-on { color:#0a7d3f; background:#dcfce7; } .f-watch { color:#b4690e; background:#fef3c7; }

  .f-seat { position:absolute; width:186px; z-index:3; background:var(--card,#fff); border:1px solid var(--line,#e6e8ec); border-radius:13px; padding:10px 12px; box-shadow:0 8px 22px -10px rgba(20,22,28,.22); }
  .f-seat-top { display:flex; gap:9px; align-items:center; }
  .f-av { width:30px; height:30px; border-radius:8px; flex:none; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; font-weight:800; font-size:12px; color:#fff; font-family:'Schibsted Grotesk',sans-serif; }
  .f-nm { font-family:'Schibsted Grotesk',sans-serif; font-weight:700; font-size:12.5px; color:var(--ink,#14161c); line-height:1.1; }
  .f-rl { font-size:10px; color:var(--ink-mute,#888c96); margin-top:1px; }
  .f-tag { font-size:8.5px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:.05em; text-transform:uppercase; padding:1px 6px; border-radius:999px; margin-left:auto; }
  .f-tag.hu { color:var(--orange-deep,#d4540a); background:rgba(255,122,26,.12); }
  .f-tag.ag { color:var(--blue-deep,#0a56b0); background:rgba(13,125,242,.12); }
  .f-meter { margin-top:9px; }
  .f-meter-l { display:flex; justify-content:space-between; font-size:9.5px; color:var(--ink-mute,#888c96); margin-bottom:3px; }
  .f-meter-l b { font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace; color:var(--ink-soft,#494d57); font-weight:600; }
  .f-bar { height:5px; border-radius:3px; background:var(--grey,#f0f1f3); overflow:hidden; }
  .f-bar i { display:block; height:100%; border-radius:3px; transform:scaleX(0); transform-origin:left; animation:f-grow 1.3s cubic-bezier(.16,1,.3,1) forwards; }
  @keyframes f-grow { to{transform:scaleX(1);} }
  .f-seat.s1 { left:0;   top:250px; } .f-seat.s2 { left:0;   top:372px; }
  .f-seat.s3 { right:0;  top:250px; } .f-seat.s4 { right:0;  top:372px; }

  @media (max-width:980px){ .cfo-stage{ transform:scale(.84); transform-origin:top center; margin:0 auto -70px; } }
  @media (max-width:860px){
    .cfo-hero-grid{ justify-content:center; }
    .cfo-hero-copy{ text-align:center; min-width:0; }
    .cfo-cta-row{ justify-content:center; }
    .cfo-trust-strip{ justify-content:center; }
    .cfo-stage{ display:none; }
  }
</style>

<!-- ================= HERO ================= -->
<section class="cfo-hero">
  <div class="cfo-hero-wrap">
    <div class="cfo-hero-grid">
      <div class="cfo-hero-copy">
        <div class="cfo-eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:16px;"><span class="cfo-tick"></span>For CFOs &amp; finance leaders</div>
        <h1 class="cfo-h1">AI is now a line item on your P&amp;L. Can you prove its <span class="accent-g">return</span>?</h1>
        <p class="cfo-lead" style="margin-top:20px;max-width:36rem;">Tokens, agents, copilots: the spend is real and growing. What no one can show you is the return: which of it moved a number, and which is just burn. OTP puts a <em>cost</em> and a <em>result</em> on every seat -- human or agent -- so spend finally connects to contribution.</p>
        <p class="cfo-body" style="margin-top:14px;max-width:36rem;">Every seat on the P&amp;L costs money. The question the operating system never answered is which seats move the needle.</p>
        <div class="cfo-cta-row">
          <a href="https://calendly.com/dawson-orgtp/30min" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cfo-btn primary">Book a walkthrough &rarr;</a>
          <a href="/trust" class="cfo-btn ghost">See the controls</a>
        </div>
        <div class="cfo-trust-strip">
          <span>Your keys, <b>your rates</b></span><span style="color:#cfd3da;">&middot;</span>
          <span>Append-only audit</span><span style="color:#cfd3da;">&middot;</span>
          <span>SOC&nbsp;2 in progress</span><span style="color:#cfd3da;">&middot;</span>
          <span>EU data residency</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- animated scene: every seat carries a cost + a number, rolling up to the plan -->
      <div class="cfo-stage">
        <svg class="f-conn" viewBox="0 0 560 500">
          <path pathLength="1" d="M150,300 C150,210 250,150 282,128" stroke="var(--orange,#ff7a1a)" style="animation-delay:.7s"/>
          <path pathLength="1" d="M150,400 C150,250 250,160 282,134" stroke="var(--orange,#ff7a1a)" style="animation-delay:.85s"/>
          <path pathLength="1" d="M410,300 C410,210 310,150 278,128" stroke="var(--blue,#0d7df2)" style="animation-delay:.9s"/>
          <path pathLength="1" d="M410,400 C410,250 310,160 278,134" stroke="var(--blue,#0d7df2)" style="animation-delay:1.05s"/>
          <circle r="3.5" fill="var(--orange,#ff7a1a)"><animateMotion dur="3s" repeatCount="indefinite" begin="1.8s" path="M150,300 C150,210 250,150 282,128"/></circle>
          <circle r="3.5" fill="var(--blue,#0d7df2)"><animateMotion dur="3s" repeatCount="indefinite" begin="2.4s" path="M410,400 C410,250 310,160 278,134"/></circle>
        </svg>

        <div class="f-board pop" style="animation-delay:.4s">
          <div class="f-board-h"><div class="f-board-t">Operating plan &middot; Q3</div><span class="f-live"><i></i>EXAMPLE</span></div>
          <div class="f-kpi"><div class="f-kpi-name"><span class="f-owner" style="background:#e07a3a">B</span>Gross margin</div><span class="f-kpi-val">+3.1 pts</span><span class="f-pill f-on">on&nbsp;track</span></div>
          <div class="f-kpi"><div class="f-kpi-name"><span class="f-owner" style="background:#0d7df2">D</span>AI&nbsp;spend / outcome</div><span class="f-kpi-val">&minus;22%</span><span class="f-pill f-on">on&nbsp;track</span></div>
          <div class="f-kpi"><div class="f-kpi-name"><span class="f-owner" style="background:#0a9d63">T</span>Revenue per FTE</div><span class="f-kpi-val">$312K</span><span class="f-pill f-watch">watch</span></div>
        </div>

        <div class="f-seat s1 rise" style="animation-delay:.7s">
          <div class="f-seat-top"><div class="f-av" style="background:#e07a3a">SK</div><div><div class="f-nm">Sarah Kim</div><div class="f-rl">Product Manager</div></div><span class="f-tag hu">Human</span></div>
          <div class="f-meter"><div class="f-meter-l"><span>Output vs. fully-loaded cost</span><b>2.4&times;</b></div><div class="f-bar"><i style="width:88%;background:var(--orange,#ff7a1a);animation-delay:1.2s"></i></div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="f-seat s2 rise" style="animation-delay:.85s">
          <div class="f-seat-top"><div class="f-av" style="background:#c4612a">AR</div><div><div class="f-nm">Alex Rivera</div><div class="f-rl">RevOps Lead</div></div><span class="f-tag hu">Human</span></div>
          <div class="f-meter"><div class="f-meter-l"><span>Output vs. fully-loaded cost</span><b>1.9&times;</b></div><div class="f-bar"><i style="width:72%;background:var(--orange,#ff7a1a);animation-delay:1.35s"></i></div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="f-seat s3 rise" style="animation-delay:.95s">
          <div class="f-seat-top"><div class="f-av" style="background:#0d7df2">RA</div><div><div class="f-nm">Research Agent</div><div class="f-rl">$ spend tracked</div></div><span class="f-tag ag">Agent</span></div>
          <div class="f-meter"><div class="f-meter-l"><span>Spend &rarr; value</span><b>3.1&times;</b></div><div class="f-bar"><i style="width:84%;background:var(--blue,#0d7df2);animation-delay:1.45s"></i></div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="f-seat s4 rise" style="animation-delay:1.1s">
          <div class="f-seat-top"><div class="f-av" style="background:#0a64c4">WF</div><div><div class="f-nm">Workflow Agent</div><div class="f-rl">$ spend tracked</div></div><span class="f-tag ag">Agent</span></div>
          <div class="f-meter"><div class="f-meter-l"><span>Spend &rarr; value</span><b>0.8&times;</b></div><div class="f-bar"><i style="width:30%;background:#d97706;animation-delay:1.55s"></i></div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ================= THE RETURN GAP ================= -->
<section class="cfo-grey">
  <div class="cfo-wrap cfo-sec">
    <div class="cfo-max720">
      <div class="cfo-eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:16px;">The return gap</div>
      <h2 class="cfo-h2">AI has a spend line. It doesn't have a return line.</h2>
      <p class="cfo-body" style="margin-top:18px;max-width:44rem;">You can total the AI bill to the dollar: seats, tokens, subscriptions. What you can't do is tie a dollar of it to a result. That's a cost growing on your P&amp;L with no ROI line next to it, and the board is about to ask.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cfo-grid3 reveal">
      <div class="cfo-card">
        <span class="cfo-chip" style="background:rgba(220,38,38,.1);"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#dc2626" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M12 2v20"/><path d="M17 5H9.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 0 7h5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 0 7H6"/></svg></span>
        <h3>Cost you can see, return you can't</h3>
        <p>Every usage report ends at the invoice. None of them tell you whether the spend changed a number you report, so you're funding a line you can't defend.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cfo-card">
        <span class="cfo-chip" style="background:rgba(217,119,6,.12);"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#d97706" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><rect x="2" y="6" width="20" height="13" rx="2"/><path d="M2 10h20M6 15h4"/></svg></span>
        <h3>Agents spend money on their own</h3>
        <p>Micro-payments are where the agent economy is heading -- agents with budgets, a credit card, and no human telling them to spend. It isn't here yet, but when it arrives, spend without controls is an unbudgeted line that grows while you sleep.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cfo-card">
        <span class="cfo-chip" style="background:rgba(13,125,242,.1);"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#0d7df2" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M16 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H6a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M22 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.9M16 3.1a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.8"/></svg></span>
        <h3>Headcount math is now hybrid</h3>
        <p>Your model has FTEs. It doesn't have agents: a new class of labor with real cost and real output. You can't plan a workforce you can't see, cost, or compare.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ================= ONE OPERATING SYSTEM ================= -->
<section class="cfo-paper">
  <div class="cfo-wrap cfo-sec">
    <div class="cfo-max720">
      <div class="cfo-eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:16px;">One operating system</div>
      <h2 class="cfo-h2">A cost and a number on every seat -- person or agent.</h2>
      <p class="cfo-body" style="margin-top:18px;max-width:44rem;">OTP puts your whole org -- people and agents -- on one accountability map, and rolls every KPI up to your operating plan: the 3&ndash;5 year targets and the one number this quarter. Each seat carries what it costs and the result it drives. For the first time, finance can answer the only question that matters: <strong style="color:var(--ink,#14161c);">is this seat earning its cost?</strong></p>
    </div>
    <div class="cfo-grid2 reveal">
      <div class="cfo-card">
        <h3>Cost-to-contribution, per seat</h3>
        <p>Hold an agent to the same scorecard as a person: a role, a number it owns, and what it costs to run. The 0.8&times; agents get retired; the 3&times; ones get scaled. Spend follows return, not the other way around.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cfo-card">
        <h3>A living plan, not a static spreadsheet</h3>
        <p>Your operating plan stops being a board deck that's stale by Tuesday. Humans and agents drive the same numbers, and the plan updates as the work actually happens, rolled up in real time.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cfo-card">
        <h3>Capacity you can actually see</h3>
        <p>See how much of the business already runs without a person touching it, where you're over- or under-resourced, and the dependency gaps that quietly cost you, without chasing a single status update.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cfo-card">
        <h3>Build vs. buy vs. agent -- with data</h3>
        <p>When the next role opens, decide person or agent on evidence: what each costs, what each returns, and what the work actually requires. The most expensive headcount decision becomes a measured one.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ================= SPEND GOVERNANCE & CONTROLS ================= -->
<section class="cfo-grey">
  <div class="cfo-wrap cfo-sec">
    <div class="cfo-max720">
      <div class="cfo-eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:16px;">Spend governance &amp; controls</div>
      <h2 class="cfo-h2">Built for the person who signs the checks.</h2>
      <p class="cfo-body" style="margin-top:18px;max-width:44rem;">AI without controls is an open credit card. OTP was built upstream: the financial and data controls a CFO asks for are the product, not a roadmap promise.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cfo-feat">
      <div class="cfo-feat-row"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#0d7df2" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/><path d="M12 7v5l3 2"/></svg><div><b>Visibility into agent spend</b><span>Every agent sits in a seat with an owner and a number, so its cost lands where you can see it. Agent-initiated payments (micro-payments, Stripe) are where this is heading, not what ships today -- the accountability structure is built ahead of the spend.</span></div></div>
      <div class="cfo-feat-row"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#0d7df2" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M15 7h3a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v9a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H6a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V9a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h3"/><path d="M9 7V5a3 3 0 0 1 6 0v2"/></svg><div><b>Your keys, your negotiated rates</b><span>Plug in your enterprise API key. AI runs on your account, at your minimums and your discounts, with no reseller markup sitting between you and the model.</span></div></div>
      <div class="cfo-feat-row"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#0d7df2" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M9 11l3 3 8-8"/><path d="M20 12v6a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H6a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V6a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h9"/></svg><div><b>Append-only audit trail</b><span>Every change is recorded and immutable. How data is created, deleted, and retained is documented in plain English: the controls trail your auditors will ask for.</span></div></div>
      <div class="cfo-feat-row"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#0d7df2" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><rect x="4" y="10" width="16" height="11" rx="2"/><path d="M8 10V7a4 4 0 0 1 8 0v3"/></svg><div><b>Private data, no model training</b><span>Turn on private mode and your financials, KPIs, and scorecards stay yours; we never learn from them, and you control who has access, down through the org.</span></div></div>
      <div class="cfo-feat-row"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#0d7df2" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/><path d="M2 12h20M12 3a15 15 0 0 1 0 18M12 3a15 15 0 0 0 0 18"/></svg><div><b>SOC&nbsp;2 &amp; EU residency</b><span>SOC&nbsp;2 underway, hosted in the EU on PostgreSQL&nbsp;16 + Cloudflare&nbsp;R2. Full trust documentation on request.</span></div></div>
      <div class="cfo-feat-row"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#0d7df2" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M3 7h18M3 12h18M3 17h18"/></svg><div><b>One layer, not more SaaS sprawl</b><span>It consolidates the operating view instead of adding another point tool to the stack you're already trying to rationalize. Humans are free. Agents are $16 a seat, flat -- the first pricing model where the ledger can show what each seat returns.</span></div></div>
    </div>
    <p class="cfo-body" style="margin-top:22px;font-size:14.5px;">And no lock-in: your data is yours, exportable on request today, and importing from Ninety or Bloom Growth takes an afternoon -- so the cost of trying it is a walkthrough, not a migration.</p>
    <div style="margin-top:30px;"><a href="/trust" class="cfo-btn ghost">See the full trust &amp; controls model &rarr;</a></div>
  </div>
</section>

